- Use Elixir style guide (https://github.com/christopheradams/elixir_style_guide).
- Pipe first, then pattern match:
  - Prefer pipelines when transforming data.
- Use descriptive, explicit function names.
- Avoid overusing anonymous functions.
- Document public functions with `@doc`.
- Group related functions together.
- Follow community conventions for naming and module structure.
- Use Credo to enforce style and consistency.
